        "descriptionModule": {
            "briefSummary": "A prospective, multinational, randomized, double-blind, clinical trial evaluating the safety and effectiveness of a novel atrioventricular interval modulation (AVIM) algorithm downloaded into a previously implanted dual-chamber Medtronic Astra/Azure DR MRI IPG.",
            "detailedDescription": "The study will be conducted in three phases: 1) Screening/ Run-in Phase, 2) Double-blind Randomized phase (1 year), and 3) Randomized unblinded phase (2 years). Patients within 90 days of de novo implant of a Medtronic Astra/Azure pacemaker also having uncontrolled hypertension may be approached for inclusion into this study. During the Double-blind Randomized Phase, subjects in the control group will receive standard-of-care pacemaker and hypertension therapy."
        },
